course_metadata.title: Energy: Dynamics Energy and Indoor Air Quality Simulation

content_chunks.content: This course encompasses the principles of energy dynamics and indoor air quality (IAQ) simulation, focusing on modeling techniques, IAQ parameters, and regulatory implications. Students will use advanced simulation software (e.g., IDA-ICE, OpenStudio) to create and analyze models to evaluate energy efficiency and IAQ in buildings. Digital skills relevant to the construction and engineering sectors, such as building information modeling (BIM), data analytics, and simulation software, will be emphasized.

Technology for building energy simulation and indoor air quality analysis - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in IDA-ICE and OpenStudio platforms for energy dynamics principles and IAQ parameter monitoring. Students will master advanced building energy flow analysis techniques, energy efficiency modeling, and building information modeling (BIM) integration for energy modeling techniques. The curriculum focuses on practical applications of energy simulation optimization, building performance assessment, and energy efficiency standards development. Participants will gain hands-on experience with energy simulation tools for IAQ health impacts evaluation, energy dynamics case studies, and regulatory frameworks compliance. The program emphasizes advanced simulation methods for real-world building energy analysis, energy modeling troubleshooting, and long-term performance assessment strategies using cutting-edge simulation software technologies.
